quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,We gave Abraham moral authority and We knew him well
  21,52,"Behold, he said to his father and his people, “What are these statues to which you are devoted?”"
  21,53,"They said, “We found our fathers worshipping them.”"
  21,54,"He said, “Indeed you have been in manifest error, you and your fathers.”"
  21,55,"They said, “Have you brought us the truth, or are you one of those who mock?”"
  21,56,"He said, “No, and your Lord is the Guardian Evolver of the heavens and the earth, and He is the One Who created them, and I am a witness to this"
  21,57,"“And by God, I have a plan for your idols after you go away and turn your backs.”"
  21,58,"Then he broke them to pieces, all but the biggest of them, so that they might turn to it"
  21,59,"They said, “Who has done this to our gods? He must indeed be of the wrong-doers.”"
  21,60,"They said, “We heard a youth talk of them. His name is Abraham.”"
  21,61,"They said, “Then bring him before the eyes of the people, that they may bear witness.”"
  21,62,"They said, “Are you the one who did this to our gods, O Abraham?”"
  21,63,"He said, “No, this was done by that, the biggest one. Ask them, if they can speak.”"
  21,64,"So they turned to themselves and said, “Indeed you are the ones in the wrong.”"
  21,65,"Then they were angered and embarrassed. They said, “You know full well that these do not speak.”"
  21,66,"Abraham said, “Do you then worship, besides God, things that can neither be of any good to you nor do you harm"
  21,67,"“Shame on you, and on the things that you worship besides God. Have you no sense?”"
  21,68,"They said, “Burn him and protect your gods, if you want to do something.”"
  21,69,"We said, “O fire, be cool and safe for Abraham.”"
  21,70,"Then they sought a plot against him, but We made them the ones who lost most"
  21,71,And We delivered him and Lot to the land which We have blessed for the nations
  21,72,"And We bestowed on him Isaac, and as an additional gift, Jacob, and We made righteous the people of each one of them"
  21,73,"And We made them leaders, guiding the people by Our command, and We sent them inspiration to do good deeds, to establish prayer, and to give zakat, and they constantly served Us"
  21,74,"And to Lot, We gave judgment and knowledge, and We saved him from the town which practiced abominations. Truly they were a people given to wrong, a rebellious people"
  21,75,"And We admitted him to Our mercy, for he was one of the righteous"
  21,76,"And Noah, when he cried, We listened to him, and delivered him and his family from great distress"
  21,77,We helped him against the people who rejected Our signs. Truly they were a people given to wrong. So We drowned them all
  21,78,"And remember David and Solomon, when they gave judgment in the matter of the field, into which the sheep of certain people had strayed by night. We did witness their judgment"
  21,79,"To Solomon We inspired the understanding of the matter. To each We gave judgment and knowledge, it was Our power that made the hills and the birds praise Us with David. It was We Who did it"
  21,80,"It was We Who taught him the making of armor for your benefit, to guard you from violence. Will you then be grateful"
  21,81,"The violent wind flowed for Solomon, by his order to the land which We had blessed, for We know all things"
  21,82,"And of the devils were some who dived for him, and did other work besides that, and it was We Who guarded them"